adolph frederick rupp (september 2, 1901 â€“ december 10, 1977) was one of the most successful coaches in the history of american college basketball. rupp is ranked fourth (behind mike krzyzewski, bob knight, and dean smith) in total victories by a men's ncaa division i college coach, winning 876 games in 41 years of coaching. rupp is also second among all men's college coaches in all-time winning percentage (.822), trailing only clair bee. rupp was enshrined in the naismith memorial basketball hall of fame on april 13, 1969.